Nigerian clergyman, Chukwuemeka Ohanaemere aka Prophet Odumeje has paid a visit to the wife of late founder of Synagogue Church Of All Nations (SCOAN) TB Joshua.  Recall that the powerful man of God died on June 5, 2021, and was buried in Lagos on July 9. Odumeje is General Overseer of The Mountain of Holy Ghost Intervention and Deliverance Ministry in Anambra. On Tuesday, the church shared a video of the controversial cleric’s visit to Joshua’s residence. Odumeje was received by the wife, Evelyn. He consoled the widow and offered prayers for the family and the Synagogue Church. Evelyn, a preacher and counsellor, is expected to take over as a SCOAN leader. Until now, she stayed away from the limelight. Evelyn is described as a humble person like Joshua. Their 31 years of marriage produced 3 children. Video of Odumeje’s visit:  The family of the late Nigerian clergyman, Prophet TB Joshua has requested active participation of the Lagos State government during the burial of the founder of the Synagogue Church of All Nations (SCOAN), Sun News reports. The widow, Evelyn made the appeal when Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu paid a condolence visit… In "News" Evelyn, wife of the late founder of the Synagogue Church of All Nations, Prophet Temitope Joshua, aka TB Joshua, on Wednesday, said the death of her husband was an act of God. She spoke when a delegate from the Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, led by the Commissioner for Home… In "Features" TB Joshua and Evelyn Evelyn, wife of the founder of the Synagogue Church of All Nationd, SCOAN, Pastor Temitope Balogun Joshua,  popularly known as T.B Joshua,  has given graphic and precise description of the last moments of her husband- how he died. Evelyn spoke with a select group of journalists… In "Metro"